  <refnamediv>
    <refname>Libration Point</refname>

    <refpurpose>A libration point.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <synopsis>Create LibrationPoint <replaceable>name</replaceable>
<replaceable>name</replaceable>.<replaceable>field</replaceable> = <replaceable>value</replaceable>
Â…</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>

    <para>The object Libration Point allows you to add a special point that
    can be used as a reference point or a point to be used for the plots. The
    libration point, also called a Lagrange point, is a point in space that a
    satellite can orbit about even though there is no central body. it is a
    phenomenon of a three-body system. It is part of the resource tree and can
    be added under Solar System.</para>
  </refsection>
  
  <refsection>
    <title>Fields</title>
    
    <variablelist>
        <varlistentry>
            <term>Primary</term>

            <listitem>
                <para>The Primary field tells GMAT
            which body to consider the primary body in the calculation of the
            location of a libration point.</para>
                
                <variablelist spacing="compact">
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term>Default</term>
                        
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Sun</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                    
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term>Limits</term>
                        
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Sun, Mercury,
            Venus, Earth, Luna, Mars, Jupiter, Saturn, Uranus, Neptune,
            Pluto, or any Barycenter. ( The Primary and Secondary bodies
            cannot be the same )</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                    
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term>Units</term>
                        
                        <listitem>
                            <para>N/A</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                </variablelist>
            </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        
        <varlistentry>
            <term>Secondary</term>

            <listitem>
                <para>The Secondary field
            tells GMAT which body to consider the secondary body in the
            calculation of the location of a libration point.</para>
                
                <variablelist spacing="compact">
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term>Default</term>
                        
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Earth</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                    
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term>Limits</term>
                        
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Sun, Mercury, Venus, Earth, Luna, Mars, Jupiter, Saturn, Uranus,
            Neptune, Pluto, or any Barycenter. ( The Primary and Secondary
            bodies cannot be the same )</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                    
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term>Units</term>
                        
                        <listitem>
                            <para>N/A</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                </variablelist>
            </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        
        <varlistentry>
            <term>Point</term>

            <listitem>
                <para>The Point field specifies which libration point
            the object corresponds to.</para>
                
                <variablelist spacing="compact">
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term>Default</term>
                        
                        <listitem>
                            <para>L1</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                    
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term>Limits</term>
                        
                        <listitem>
                            <para>L1, L2, L3, L4, L5</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                    
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term>Units</term>
                        
                        <listitem>
                            <para>N/A</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                </variablelist>
            </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsection>
  
  <refsection>
      <title>Interactions</title>

      <variablelist>
        <varlistentry>
          <term>Coordinate System</term>

            <listitem>
              <para>Interacts with libration point in that libration point can
              be selected as the origin of the coordinate system or as a
              primary or secondary point for defining the axes.</para>
            </listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        <varlistentry>
          <term>OpenGL plot</term>

            <listitem>
              <para>Interacts with a libration point in a number of ways. It
              can be selected as a celestial object to be drawn onto the plot.
              A libration point can also be selected as the View Point
              Reference or the View Direction.</para>
            </listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        <varlistentry>
          <term>Barycenter</term>

            <listitem>
              <para>Interacts with a libration point in that the bary center
              can be selected as the primary or secondary body for calculating
              the libration point.</para>
            </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
      </variablelist>
    </refsection>
    
  <refsection>
    <title>Examples</title>

    <refsection>
      <title>Script Syntax</title>

      <programlisting><code>
Create Libration Point;
.Primary = ;
.Secondary = ;
.Point = &lt;'L1', 'L2', 'L3', 'L4', 'L5'&gt;</code></programlisting>
    </refsection>

    <refsection>
      <title>Sample Script</title>

      <programlisting><code>Create LibrationPoint Libration1;
GMAT Libration1.Primary = Sun;
GMAT Libration1.Secondary = Earth;
GMAT Libration1.Point = 'L1';</code></programlisting>
    </refsection>
  </refsection>
